CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, September 20, 1958, pg. B6, reads: "Florida Visitor - Samuel J. McCall (seated in center) of Tampa, Fla. was honored at a dinner party given by Mr. and Mrs. George Lawrence, recently. Mr. McCall, carving the turkey, is the Grand Traveling Deputy and Past Exalted Ruler of Bay City Lodge 8, Tampa.  His is also State Director of the Junior Herd, IBPOEW.  Flanking him are Lorena Williams, left, and Helen Lawrence (the hostess), right.  Standing left to right: Charles Ross, Esther Young, Atty. Joseph Givens, Alice Farris, George Lawrence and Leo McTurner, exalted Ruler of Iron City Lodge. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of women and men at dinner party, seated from left: Lorena Williams, Samuel J. McCall carving turkey, Helen Lawrence; standing: Charles Ross, Esther Young, Atty. Joseph Givens, Alice Farris, George Lawrence, and Leo McTurner, in Lawrence home, another version
